data.text: I understand why broadcast mets have to stick to the NHC forecast. That said, I still believe that all of South Florida excluding the Lower Keys is still in danger of AT LEAST tropical storm impacts and residents should be ready to act on a dime.

@dos_rositas @JohnMoralesNBC6 I'd have them ready. Remember, the cone has shifted back west and 1/3 of the time the storm will end up somewhere outside the cone. I'd say the only place in South Florida not in danger of at least tropical storm force winds is the Keys. I understand why John has to stick to NHC.

“If that storm keeps heading West as it is, I’m really afraid for people here on this island, because there are people who are still fixing their roofs from the last hurricane,” said 26 y/o Max Devine from Bimini. He has not been able to reach friends in Abaco Islands for hours.
